<legis-type>A BILL</legis-type> 
<official-title>To amend title 31, United States Code, to require the Secretary of the Treasury to provide for the purchase of paper United States savings bonds with tax refunds.</official-title> 
</form> 
<legis-body id="H395390CF4A7E4AEA8CBCE6AF36A3EE4E" style="OLC"> 
<section id="HDC93A9BA8DF4468AB278DE30EE7D0653" section-type="section-one">
      <enum>1.</enum>
      <header>Short title</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the <quote>
          <short-title>Save Access to a Valuable Investment Needed to Generate Savings Act of 2013</short-title>
        </quote> or the <quote>
          <short-title>SAVINGS Act</short-title>
        </quote>.</text>
    </section> 
<section id="HB0864869B6BD4B518BAC2258B3158AFB">
      <enum>2.</enum>
      <header>Purchase paper United States savings bonds with tax refund</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">
        <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="uscode" value="usc/31/3106">
          <external-xref legal-doc="usc" parsable-cite="usc/31/3106">Section 3106</external-xref> of title 31, United States Code</cato:entity-ref>, is amended by adding at the end the following:</text> 
<quoted-block style="USC" id="H24C9187567564324918F1A707AEB573B" display-inline="no-display-inline"> 
<subsection id="H6309A4766DC84B63BC68B1448B9B2BD4">
          <enum>(d)</enum> 
<paragraph id="HA9F2CBCA2E214A46BC8D9E347086D051" display-inline="yes-display-inline">
            <enum>(1)</enum>
            <text>During the period ending on December 31, 2018, the <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="federal-body" entity-id="2000">Secretary</cato:entity-ref> shall provide an option on individual returns of tax under <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Internal Revenue Code of 1986/st:A">subtitle A of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986</cato:entity-ref> to purchase United States savings bonds in paper form with a portion or all of a refund of overpayment of such tax for the purchaser or anyone.</text>
          </paragraph> 
<paragraph id="H38CE719926344E2481EF8FAF8C809863" indent="up1">
            <enum>(2)</enum>
            <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">
              <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="uscode" value="usc/31/3106/d/1" proposed="true">Paragraph (1)</cato:entity-ref> shall not apply if the Secretary implements an alternative option which—</text> 
<subparagraph id="HACD7B2AED1FC4725A098903E310D60DB">
              <enum>(A)</enum>
              <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">allows for the gifting of United States savings bonds,</text>
            </subparagraph> 
<subparagraph id="HC0B9D697BDB5465E99275E14D243CE34">
              <enum>(B)</enum>
              <text>serves the unbanked, and</text>
            </subparagraph> 
<subparagraph id="H0B68C6AF8DBE4CF6A58EB1C3859B3AAF">
              <enum>(C)</enum>
              <text>retains the ability to sign-up on the return of tax.</text>
            </subparagraph>
          </paragraph>
        </subsection>
        <after-quoted-block>.</after-quoted-block>
      </quoted-block>
    </section> 
